Based on administrative records from the Washington State Impaired Driver
 Testing Program, 19992007.
 The histogram height on the vertical axis is based on frequency of observations
, with BAC on the horizontal axis.
 The vertical black lines represent the two legal thresholds at 0.08 and
 0.15.
 The bin width is 0.001, the original precision used on the breathalyzers.
